{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An adaptive backend which uses different backends under the hood depending on the target operating system."}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The beauty of SwiftCrossUI is that you can write your app once and have it look native everywhere. For this reason I recommend using DefaultBackend unless you’ve got particular constraints. It uses ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","type":"reference"},{"text":" on macOS, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","type":"reference"},{"text":" on Window, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","type":"reference"},{"text":" on Linux, and on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","type":"reference"},{"text":" on iOS\/tvOS.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re using DefaultBackend, you can override the underlying backend during compilation by setting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SCUI_DEFAULT_BACKEND","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable to the name of the desired backend. This is useful when you e.g. want to test the Gtk version of your app while using a Mac. Note that this only works for built-in backends and still requires the chosen backend to be compatible with your machine."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"Warning","style":"warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SCUI_DEFAULT_BACKEND"},{"text":" to switch underlying backends, you may encounter some linker-related missing symbol errors. These are caused by a SwiftPM bug and usually disappear if you run ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift package clean"},{"text":" before attempting to build your app again.","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage","type":"heading","level":2},{"code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: \"DefaultBackend\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","      ]","    )","    ...","  ]","  ...",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 1: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"adding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" to an executable target"}]}]},{"code":["import SwiftCrossUI","import DefaultBackend","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","  \/\/ You can explicitly initialize your app's chosen backend if you desire.","  \/\/ This happens automatically when you import any of the built-in backends.","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = DefaultBackend()","","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      Text(\"Hello, World!\")","        .padding()","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 2: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultBackend"}],"type":"emphasis"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/defaultbackend"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"DefaultBackend","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generat